  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 9 airports right now. Engine anti-ice operations are flagged at Suceava Stefan cel Mare (SCV/LRSV). Across base airports: 4 critical, 11 high, 7 medium, 17 normal. Key bases needing attention include Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR), Chişinău (RMO/LUKK) and Iaşi (IAS/LRIA); plus 12 other bases. 7 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is mist, fog / freezing fog and very low visibility  — most notably around Suceava Stefan cel Mare (SCV/LRSV), Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP) and Craiova (CRA/LRCV). Network hotspots: Suceava Stefan cel Mare (SCV/LRSV), Lennart Meri Tallinn (TLL/EETN), Turku (TKU/EFTU), Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM), Milan Bergamo Airport / Antonio Locatelli Air Base (BGY/LIME) and 4 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, RVR limitations and approach minima limits. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Suceava Stefan cel Mare (SCV/LRSV), Lennart Meri Tallinn (TLL/EETN), Turku (TKU/EFTU) and 9 others.",
